Jared -

Attached is our first attempt at a partner profitability model for the CardConnect gateway.
We will need to get together to review the CardConnect deals to determine where they each fall
within the model since pricing varies.

Also, since we are not automatically calculating partner residuals with the CardConnect platform,
it made the calculations in the model difficult. If necessary, we can continue to build out this
model to figure out an average discount to expect when partners are paid.

Please let me know your thoughts and when you might be available to dive in deeper on the
numbers.

Overview
•	 On 1/14/19 at 8:22 PM, Card Connect employee, Jared Isaacman (jared@shift4.com) sent his
notice of resignation to Card Connect.
•	 During the subsequent 2 weeks, emails and other files were sent to various Shift4 accounts,
including but not limited to:
o Corporate account
o Personal accounts
•	 The most concerning email, discussed in this presentation, was sent at 8:24 AM, just 2
minutes after the resignation was sent. This email included the following attachment.
o	CardConnect Gateway Potential Partner Profitability – First Draft.xlsx: This report
contains sensitive and proprietary formulas which the Shift4 team should not have
